{"default_url":null,"content":{"state":0,"taskInstructions":null,"references":[],"isTaskInstructionsVisible":true,"isCommentMandatory":false,"fields":[],"masterFinding":{"id":2989394,"exploitInstructions":"","verificationInstructions":"<b>Verification Instructions</b>\n\nCheck if any of the following best practices are missing. The lack of CAPTCHA, by itself, does not warrant a vulnerability.\n<ol><li>Allow users to start the password recovery process by entering their email address on the reset page.</li>\n<li>Require users to fill in a captcha, and return a message stating &quot;Your request has been processed&quot; for both valid and non-existing user accounts.</li>\n<li>Send an email to the user containing an URL with a unique, one-time token. The token links the password reset request to the user's account. The token should expire in 15 minutes or less. However, expiration up to 3 hours is acceptable but a shorter expiration is recommended.</li>\n<li>The password reset page should not authenticate the user to the application; it should only allow a password reset.</li>\n<li>Invalidate the token after it has been used once.</li>\n</ol>\n<b>Reporting Requirements</b>\n<ol><li>Add an explanation how the password reset process works in the application and which controls are missing</li>\n<li>Add screenshots for each step of the password reset process highlighting the weaknesses</li>\n</ol>\n","remediationInstructions":"Implement the following password recovery process:\n<ol><li>Allow users to start the password recovery process by entering their email address on the reset page.</li>\n<li>Require users to fill in a captcha and return a message stating &quot;Your request has been processed&quot; for both valid and non-existing user accounts.</li>\n<li>Send an email to the user containing a URL with a unique, one-time token. The token links the password reset request to the user's account. The token should expire in less than 3 hours but a shorted expiration time, like 15 minutes, is recommended.</li>\n<li>The password reset page should not authenticate the user to the application; it should only allow a password reset.</li>\n<li>Invalidate the token after it has been used once.</li>\n</ol>\n","name":"Weak Password Reset or Recovery Functionality","sourceId":"M:2989394","severity":"Medium","businessImpact":"Weak password reset or recovery functionality may allow attackers to gain unauthorized access to application user accounts.  ","description":"The password recovery process is currently missing best practice security controls.\n"}}}